      "textZh": "观李君《不稳定轮廓》，题名已显哲思——何为「轮廓」？界限也、边界也、定义也。然「不稳定」三字，将确定性消解。此正合佛家「诸法无我」之理、道家「道可道，非常道」之义。万物皆流动，界限皆虚设。吾尝言「横看成岭侧成峰」，物之形态因视角而异，何来固定轮廓？此作若能让观者体验这种「界限的消融」「形态的流变」，则可引发对「本质」「身份」「存在」的深思。然不稳定若过度，则导致虚无；流变若无度，则失去把握。建议在「稳定」与「不稳定」之间找到张力——让形态既流动又可识别、既变化又有规律。如水之流动，虽无定形，却有其势；如云之变幻，虽不可测，却有其理。",
      "textEn": "Observing Li Jun's 'Unstable Contours,' the title显 philosophical thinking—what is 'contour'? Boundary, border, definition. Yet 'unstable' three characters dissolve certainty. This accords with Buddhism's 'all dharmas are without self' principle, Daoism's 'the way that can be spoken is not the eternal way' meaning. All things flow, boundaries are虚设. I once said 'viewed horizontally as ridge, sideways as peak'; things' forms differ by perspective, where comes fixed contour? If this work can让观者 experience this 'boundary dissolution,' 'form transformation,' it can provoke deep thought about 'essence,' 'identity,' 'existence.' Yet if instability is excessive, it leads to nihilism; if transformation is unlimited, grasp is lost. I suggest finding tension between 'stable' and 'unstable'—让形态 both flowing and recognizable, both changing and patterned. Like water's flow, though formless, has its momentum; like clouds' transformation, though unpredictable, has its principles.",
